The purpose of the BLOCk-CTI study is to evaluate the safety and effectiveness of the Blazer(R) Open-Irrigated Ablation Catheter for the treatment of sustained or recurrent type 1 atrial flutter.

 This study will compare outcomes in patients treated with the Blazer(R) Open-Irrigated Ablation Catheter to outcomes in patients treated with open-irrigated radiofrequency ablation catheters that have received FDA market approval for the treatment of type 1 atrial flutter.

